Nigerian Military High Command says troops of Operation Whirl Stroke have killed five bandits and arrested eight others in Benue and Nasarawa States. A statement by the Coordinator Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche indicates that four of the bandits were eliminated during a raid on their hideout in Tse Agi, Gwer West LGA of Benue State. Enenche notes that one of the bandits met his waterloo when troops stormed their camp along Benue-Nasarawa border. Several arms were recovered during the encounter. The Military commended the public for providing credible intelligence information that facilitated the successful operation.